				Elial Brook ain't difficult. I was a lvl 4 mage, was grouped with lvl 4 necro. We were in luck that both our pets conned yellow to ourselves ... kewl! I attacked Elial, and he feared me so that I lost control over myself and ran all over the show. Hunting partner couldn't keep up, and she was anyway asking something from the guard. However, my pet also followed, and eventually Elial had to turn to pet. That gave me time to recover. Managed to SERIOUSLY beat the crap outta him. Ok, so I survived with having only 1 1/2 bub hp left, and pet down to approx 40%, but for our level we got good exp. What am I trying to say? You can take out Elial if you are lvl 4, a good burn spell (NOT Burst of Flame) and at least white con pet. He is fun to kill! As for the gloves ... they are ok, just a bit heavy. The only real use of them is saving your exp in should you happen to die. Guess this is handy =0)<BR>
From lvl 8 onwards you don't really get exp for the dude, at least not worth the effort.
